---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="The formal academic framework behind the Halmetoja Model — the Structural Regulation Framework (SRF)."
>
  <article class="research">
    <header class="research-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Academic Foundation</p>
      <h1>Research</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The Halmetoja Model uses CENTER/ORBIT terminology for accessibility.
        The formal academic framework is called the <strong>Structural Regulation Framework (SRF)</strong>.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="bridge">
      <h2>Two languages, one architecture</h2>
      <p>
        The popular articles on this site use CENTER and ORBIT as intuitive labels
        for regulation location. The academic paper uses precise construct definitions
        designed for empirical testing and falsification.
      </p>

      <div class="mapping">
        <div class="map-row">
          <span class="map-popular">CENTER</span>
          <span class="map-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="map-academic">Internal Regulation Capacity (IRC)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="map-row">
          <span class="map-popular">ORBIT</span>
          <span class="map-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="map-academic">External Regulation Dependence (ERD)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="map-row">
          <span class="map-popular">Integration</span>
          <span class="map-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="map-academic">Structural Flexibility (SF)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="map-row">
          <span class="map-popular">Speed of externalization</span>
          <span class="map-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="map-academic">Regulation Externalization Latency (REL)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="map-row">
          <span class="map-popular">ORBIT channels</span>
          <span class="map-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="map-academic">Externalization Vectors (EV)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        The relationship is not one-to-one renaming. The academic framework introduces
        orthogonal dimensions (IRC × SF), structural levels, falsifiability criteria,
        and a dynamic process variable (REL) proposed as the framework's primary
        empirical contribution.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="papers">
      <h2>Papers</h2>

      <div class="paper-card">
        <div class="paper-info">
          <h3>Structural Regulation Framework v2.0</h3>
          <p class="paper-subtitle">
            A Dimensional Model of Internal Regulation Capacity, Structural Flexibility, and Externalization Dynamics
          </p>
          <p class="paper-meta">
            Halmetoja, J. (2026). Preprint.
          </p>
          <p class="paper-desc">
            The full conceptual architecture: two orthogonal capacity axes (IRC, SF),
            a dynamic process variable (REL), externalization vectors, tension ontology,
            testable hypotheses, and explicit falsifiability criteria.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="paper-actions">
          <a href="/SRF-v2.0.pdf" class="button button-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Download PDF
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="status">
      <h2>Current status</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Conceptual framework:</strong> complete (v2.0)</li>
        <li><strong>Empirical validation:</strong> not yet begun</li>
        <li><strong>REL measurement paradigm:</strong> proposed, untested</li>
        <li><strong>Preprint submission:</strong> pending</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The framework is a proto-theoretical contribution — conceptually coherent,
        explicitly falsifiable, but not yet empirically validated. Its fate depends
        primarily on whether REL demonstrates independent predictive value beyond
        existing constructs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="collaboration">
      <h2>Collaboration</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a researcher interested in testing REL, validating the IRC/SF
        distinction, or exploring the framework empirically, I welcome contact.
      </p>
      <p>
        Particularly valuable would be collaboration with psychometricians,
        personality researchers, or clinical scientists with access to experimental
        paradigms and participant pools.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .research {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .research-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  p, li {
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  li strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .bridge {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .mapping {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .map-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .map-row + .map-row {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .map-popular {
    min-width: 180px;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .map-arrow {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .map-academic {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .paper-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .paper-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .paper-subtitle {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .paper-meta {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .paper-desc {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .paper-actions {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .button:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .button-primary {
    background: rgba(126, 184, 224, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(126, 184, 224, 0.35);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .button-primary:hover {
    background: rgba(126, 184, 224, 0.2);
    border-color: rgba(126, 184, 224, 0.55);
  }

  .status, .collaboration {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .map-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }

    .map-popular {
      min-width: unset;
    }

    .map-arrow {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
